Safety_Information.general_Info: Causes eye irritation. Harmful if absorbed through skin. Harmful if swallowed. Avoid contact with eyes, skin, or clothing.
Safety_Information.if_In_Eyes: Hold eye open and rinse slowly and gently with water for 15-20 minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present, after first 5 minutes, then continue rinsing.
Safety_Information.if_Swallowed: Have person sip a glass of water if able to swallow. Do not induce vomiting unless told to by the poison control center or doctor. Do not give anything by mouth to an unconscious person.
Safety_Information.if_On_Skin: Remove clothing immediately if pesticide gets inside. Then wash thoroughly and put on clean clothing.
Safety_Information.physician_Note: Have the product container or label with you when calling a poison control center or doctor.
